e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[It is noteworthy that there are no human cases of cholera reported as yet.
The isolation of the O139 strain is potentially sigificant as it could
signal the spread of this emerging strain toward Europe from Asia, perhaps
via Asian immigrants. The O139 strain was first identified in India and
Bangladesh during a 1992 outbreak of cholera. - Mods.JW/ES
